"v.避免，闪避 【英】 v.避免，闪避(to avoid deliberately) 【考】 反义词：seek actively(积极寻找) 【例】 He was shunned by his former friends.(他的老朋友 们都回避着他) v. 故意避免, 闪避 = To avoid deliberately 【记】读: 闪－闪避 【反】seek actively(积极寻找); haunt(v 经常拜访)frequent(v 时常出入)－『shun』avoid(此题争议较大) 【记】音：闪 shun (v.)  Old English scunian ""to shun, avoid; abhor; desist, abstain; to hide, seek safety by concealment,"" of uncertain origin; not found in any other language. Perhaps ultimately from PIE root *skeu- ""to cover, to hide."" Related: Shunned; shunning. A shun-pike (American English, 1911) was a road constructed to avoid tolls."
